column2: A few swordsmiths creating swords and equipment for the army.
A building storing weapons and armor for the heavy troops.
A room containing valuable books and scrolls.
A shrine that represents the only true religion.
A statue that truly shows the prestige of the dynasty.
A large stock of dried and salted food.
A communal place to bake bread.
A building supplying the people with alcoholic beverages.
A deep, broad ditch, either dry or filled with water, that surrounds the castle.
Multiple Towers protecting the castle during sieges.
A fortified gateway that acts as an outer defence to the castle.
A building accompanying one of the gateways for the castle.
